1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,200
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 4]

23
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:38,600
[Four Years Ago
2019]

24
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,040
Besides the one I just mentioned,

25
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:43,200
Flight KM997,

26
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,280
please pay attention

27
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:46,720
and see if there are any passengers

28
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,520
wearing red or carrying items

29
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:50,280
featuring red from other flights.

30
00:01:50,440 --> 00:01:51,240
Keep it in mind.

31
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,720
As easy as finding a needle
in a haystack.

32
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:54,800
Quit whining.

33
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,080
One mistake can cost everything.

34
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,760
I found nothing

35
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,120
on my shift.

36
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:07,120
It's all yours now.

37
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,520
Same as always.

38
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:09,800
Got used to it.

39
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:13,760
Mr. Shen.

40
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,520
Heard you're getting promoted.

41
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,000
Hey, Zhang Dayu.

42
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:21,440
You always remind me of your dad.

43
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,440
What does it have to do with my dad?

44
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:23,720
Both are chatterboxes.

45
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:30,240
Mr. Chen won't leave the front line.

46
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,920
Otherwise, it wouldn't be me.

47
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,440
Learn from him.

48
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:35,400
And also from Guo Cong.

49
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:35,960
Alright?

50
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,560
Don't bring shame on China Customs.

51
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,920
You guys are the future here.

52
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,520
Look how pudgy you are!

53
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,000
I'm working on it.

54
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:44,520
Are you?

55
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,200
Go.

56
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,200
Excuse me, sir. Passport, please?

57
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,280
This way.

58
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,200
Excuse me.

59
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,880
Our target might be red,

60
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,400
but not everyone wearing red

61
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,720
needs to be sent to inspection.

62
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,120
Look how busy it is now.

63
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:03,680
Thanks for your cooperation.

64
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:06,680
You need to judge first and screen.

65
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:07,680
Can you?

66
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,320
In the world,

67
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,880
no smuggling is perfect.

68
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:13,480
-There's always something with their looks

69
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,840
and their movements.

70
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:17,000
Observe, and you'll see it.

71
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:17,680
Yes, sir.

72
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:22,600
Don't get trapped by red.

73
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,200
Understood.

74
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:25,800
This way.

75
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,880
Please open it.

76
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:37,840
This is Passenger Inspection Section I.

77
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:38,560
This way.

78
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:41,000
Hello. We need to check your clothes.

79
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,360
Okay, thank you.

80
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,040
Attention, everyone.

81
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,480
Flight KM997

82
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,520
has landed.

83
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,720
Passengers will be here soon.

84
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:56,680
Guo Cong, copy.

85
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,480
Dayu, copy.

86
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,480
Deng Hongxia, copy.

87
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,480
Sir.

88
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:29,200
I've got someone suspicious.

89
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,080
He's been using his phone's front camera

90
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,200
to look behind him.

91
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,800
Short-sleeved white T

92
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,400
and black sleeveless hoodie.

93
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:43,480
Blue jeans.

94
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,440
Black and white sneakers.

95
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,880
Black suitcase

96
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:47,440
and black backpack.

97
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:48,000
Over and out.

98
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,920
Deng, go help Guo Cong.

99
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:04,600
Okay.

100
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,160
Dayu, follow him.

101
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:28,960
Copy.

102
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,160
Sir, please help me with this.

103
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,520
Hello, China Customs.

104
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,520
We need to check it.

105
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:41,960
Hello.

106
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,760
We need to check your suitcase.

107
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,320
Please open it.

108
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,800
Came from Europe with so many stamps?

109
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,440
It's my hobby.

110
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,680
Gentle!

111
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:02,920
Sorry.

112
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,320
Are they expensive?

113
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,400
It's not about the money,

114
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,280
okay?

115
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:10,080
These stamps might look small and thin,

116
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,800
but these tiny pieces

117
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,160
carry a country's history and culture.

118
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:17,520
Take this set, for example.

119
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,400
This set

120
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,200
was specially issued

121
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,960
to commemorate Mozart.

122
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:22,720
The 20 stamps here

123
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:26,280
tell all about his life
and achievements.

124
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,000
I just landed.

125
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:36,480
The trip was really worth it.

126
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,880
Quite a faw stamp collectors.

127
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:42,720
I'm a stamp collector.

128
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,640
Need those from every country.

129
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,400
Can't miss them when having the chance.

130
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,640
Do they cost much?
I might buy some, too.

131
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:52,480
Not too much. Affordable.

132
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,600
These look quite new.

133
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,320
And they're odd.

134
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,640
Doesn't matter.

135
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:01,120
Their value will increase.

136
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,480
Not really.

137
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,960
The appreciation of stamps

138
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:06,120
depends not just on time

139
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,720
but more on their artistic

140
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,680
and research value.

141
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,640
Mister,

142
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:12,240
did I use your money?

143
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:14,480
The small bag, sir.

144
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,080
Hi, officer.

145
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:17,680
Can I go now?

146
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,280
Of course.

147
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,280
Thank you for your cooperation.

148
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,640
This bag

149
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:25,600
exceeds the limit, I think.

150
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,440
Got the receipt?

151
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,320
Yeah, but it's within the limit.

152
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:30,080
It only cost 355 euros.

153
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:32,480
That's less than 5,000 yuan.

154
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,640
And plus the stamps?

155
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:34,960
Come on.

156
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,720
The stamps aren't worth much.

157
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,040
All within the limit.

158
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:40,040
Go check if you don't believe me.

159
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,240
Sorry, please come with us.

160
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,160
Thank you for your cooperation.

161
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,800
Liu.

162
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:46,840
Allow me.

163
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,840
Why did you bring me here?

164
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,160
I didn't do anything.

165
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,440
Miss, are these stamps yours?

166
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,160
Yes, they're mine.

167
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,440
Then, on behalf of China Customs,
I'm telling you,

168
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,240
the test shows

169
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:16,840
these stamps contain
illegal drug ingredients

170
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:18,760
and are prohibited from entry.

171
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,120
The Criminal Law stipulates

172
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,840
that smuggling requires the offender

173
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,600
to have subjective intent
with knowledge.

174
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:25,320
If

175
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,240
you were deceived into carrying these,

176
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:29,120
unaware of the nature of the act,

177
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,120
it does not constitute smuggling.

178
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:32,080
But

179
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:32,960
if you knew

180
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,520
what you were carrying

181
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:36,440
and were aware of the nature of the act,

182
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:38,600
then you are suspected of smuggling.

183
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:39,840
I'll ask you one more time.

184
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,920
Are these stamps yours?

185
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:42,120
Think carefully before you answer.

186
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,720
They are not mine.

187
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:48,840
A man approached me earlier,

188
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:51,280
saying his items exceeded the limit,

189
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:53,520
and asking me to help bring these in.

190
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:56,080
Then he gave me 1,000 yuan.

191
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,160
I really had no idea

192
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,720
these stamps were prohibited items.

193
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:00,880
Was it a man wearing a white T,

194
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,360
a black sleeveless hoodie,

195
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,800
and blue jeans?

196
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,320
Yes, that's him.

197
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,600
Dayu, are the anti-smuggling men here?

198
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,000
They are.

199
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,240
Look carefully.

200
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,400
There are drugs on the stamp back.

201
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:50,360
Officer,

202
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,440
I really didn't know.

203
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,400
I was deceived.

204
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:56,480
He told me to meet him

205
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,920
at the Big Bowl Noodles.

206
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,280
You need to go get him!

207
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:01,480
Okay, it's alright.

208
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,480
Miss,

209
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,920
when the anti-smuggling officers
get here,

210
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,920
tell them everything you know.

211
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,800
It's gonna be okay.

212
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,000
Hello. These are her belongings.

213
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,440
She's still so young.

214
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,280
Mr. Chen,

215
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,600
that man also had stamps.

216
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,800
Why did you let him go?

217
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,920
He knew his stamps very well,

218
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,200
while this girl knew nothing.

219
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:34,560
Could it be that he knew

220
00:11:34,560 --> 00:11:36,200
carrying stamps looked suspicious,

221
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,680
so he did some homework

222
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:39,400
to learn all about those stamps?

223
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:41,760
Did you hear his ringtone?

224
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:44,560
Some classical music.

225
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:46,880
Mozart's Serenade.

226
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,440
You know that?

227
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:50,280
In our line of work,

228
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:52,120
you need to know
a little bit of everything.

229
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:54,320
So, it makes sense his luggage

230
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,920
had a high concentration of Mozart.

231
00:11:58,040 --> 00:12:01,320
Just think.
If he wanted to smuggle drugs,

232
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,480
he couldn't be so meticulous

233
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,800
as to set his ringtone

234
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,160
to Mozart, right?

235
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,800
And look at that girl.

236
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,520
She knew the price of her bag very well,

237
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:12,240
but not so much about the stamps.

238
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,440
This bag

239
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,600
exceeds the limit, I think.

240
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:17,520
It only cost 355 euros.

241
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:19,760
That's less than 5,000 yuan.

242
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,000
And plus the stamps?

243
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:22,200
Come on.

244
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,000
The stamps aren't worth much.

245
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,360
All within the limit.

246
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,800
So obviously,

247
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:29,720
she's just a temporary mule.

248
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,680
But Mr. Chen, there's one more thing.

249
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:34,760
Yes?

250
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:36,880
The suspect

251
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:38,360
needed someone to be the carrier.

252
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:39,840
Why did he choose

253
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,120
a girl wearing pink?

254
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,280
And we happen to be looking
for a smuggler

255
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:45,040
who is related to red or pink.

256
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:48,120
Is it just coincidental or intentional?

257
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:50,920
You are asking

258
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:52,200
the right question.

259
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:57,160
I think it should be a coincidence.

260
00:12:57,920 --> 00:12:58,760
Anyway,

261
00:12:58,920 --> 00:12:59,760
Shihuo,

262
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:01,480
you've reminded me.

263
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,440
That suspect

264
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,440
is probably new at this,

265
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:08,200
giving little information to his helper.

266
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,800
And he used his phone

267
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:14,680
to keep track of the girl behind him.

268
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,560
That was exactly what exposed him.

269
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,920
It was an obvious flaw.

270
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:24,480
What do you mean?

271
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,200
I got it.

272
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,440
He did that on purpose.

273
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,160
Fan, let me.

274
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:36,600
Sure.

275
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:37,840
Cong,

276
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:41,040
how many from KM997 have gone through?

277
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,880
Only a small number.

278
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:44,040
Those with little luggage.

279
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:46,600
Those with checked luggage
are still in there.

280
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:47,840
This way, please.

281
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:50,320
Sir,

282
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,120
that girl in pink

283
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,920
whom you just checked.

284
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:54,840
How did it go?

285
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:55,640
Find anything?

286
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,560
Drugs in stamps.

287
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:58,600
You should know,

288
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,680
it's gonna be a long day.

289
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:03,440
More drug smugglers?

290
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,680
I think the big one is yet to come.

291
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,400
Seriously?

292
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:08,840
This way, please.

293
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:10,960
Now, all be quiet.

294
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:11,960
Quiet.

295
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,000
Quiet. Come here.

296
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,440
Let's take a group photo here, okay?

297
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:16,040
Okay.

298
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:20,200
Let's scooch closer

299
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,760
and take a group photo. - Larry?

300
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:22,600
Who?

301
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:23,720
Larry.

302
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:24,400
You know him?

303
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:27,560
One of the best esports players
in China.

304
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,160
It looks like he just

305
